.
"Just as a gazelle or a deer is eaten, so you will eat it; the unclean and the clean alike may eat of it. -- deuteronomy 12:22
.
"Only be sure not to eat the blood, for the blood is the life, and you shall not eat the life with the flesh. -- deuteronomy 12:23
.
"You shall not eat it; you shall pour it out on the ground like water. -- deuteronomy 12:24
.
"You shall not eat it, so that it may be well with you and your sons after you, for you will be doing what is right in the sight of the LORD. -- deuteronomy 12:25
.
"Only your holy things which you may have and your votive offerings, you shall take and go to the place which the LORD chooses. -- deuteronomy 12:26
