.
So Moses the servant of the LORD died there in the land of Moab, according to the word of the LORD. -- deuteronomy 34:5
.
And He buried him in the valley in the land of Moab, opposite Beth-peor; but no man knows his burial place to this day. -- deuteronomy 34:6
.
Although Moses was one hundred and twenty years old when he died, his eye was not dim, nor his vigor abated. -- deuteronomy 34:7
.
